title: Average retail price for butter in Canada 2015 to 2019
summary: This is a grouped bar chart showing Average retail price in CAD on the Y-axis throughout 12 Months for 2015, 2016, 2017, 2018, and 2019 on the X-axis.
Over the 12 Months, the Average retail price in CAD for 2017 have been lowered whereas risen for 2016.
Out of all 5 groups, 2019 had the highest Average retail price in CAD in Month Jul and 2015 had the lowest Average retail price in CAD in Month Jul.
In Month Jun, 2017 had the maximum Average retail price in CAD and it saw the lowest in Month Mar out of all 12 Months.
